  "texts": [
    "This optimisation process is not tracking any voter's interests.",
    "Contrary to the SEME example, we have good reasons to think that frequent and granular AI polling multiplies the availability of diverse and reliable cues, which is likely to enhance autonomous choice.",
    "Coming back to the example of the voter from rural France, let us assume you are actually a teacher in high school.",
    "Searching for relevant knowledge online to inform your voting decision, you will not only see the voting propensities of your neighborhood, but also those of your relevant socio-demographic group.",
    "Before artificially intelligent polling, you had two choices: to defer to a mass aggregation of preferences (i.e., the national level) or a small set of local preferences (i.e., your family and friends)."
